ividual, a leader has better command of complexity. An individual has a capable skillset, and limitations. Understanding both the capability/capacity,"},{"role":"assistant","content":"When you talk about turning individuals into leaders, do you mean creating something like individual autonomous cells, like a decentralized organization?The thing is, I believe this can be either interpreted as giving enough understanding and power to each individual so they develop themselves and become truly useful members for the tribe OR as pseudo-anarchic kind of organization, a decentralized thing, kind of like the internet phenomenon of Anonymous.With the first interpretation, building upwards members of the tribe and getting them to a place of taking absolute personal responsibility for their lives, being capable of autonomously and sustainably grow and have their own systems in place for their development and for yielding consistently results for themselves and for moving forwards the cause of the tribe… that’s powerful and aligns with my vision and naturally will always align with the vision of any self-improvement mentor.But decentralized structures and multiple cells of command only work for very specific kinds of purposes and environments.I don’t believe we have the need to over-think all this at the moment.Things like culture, organization and logistics and politics tend to be better put into practice by empirical testing and exploration, especially at the beginning stages."}]}
