e (when done right).I'd say one of the ways to make sure you're not just resting to procrastinate work, is by only resting when you planned to rest.When you have time set aside to rest should probably change over time (at least for a bit) while you figure out when you actually need rest and when it works best to take a break for you.I'd say it just takes trial and error though."},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd this is actually a VERY powerful insight...if you schedule time to rest on advance you know for a fact you are not procrastinating but being disciplined enough to rest periodically and systematically."}]}
