e (when done right).I'd say one of the ways to make sure you're not just resting to procrastinate work, is by only resting when you planned to rest.When you have time set aside to rest should probably change over time (at least for a bit) while you figure out when you actually need rest and when it works best to take a break for you.I'd say it just takes trial and error though."},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd this is actually a VERY powerful insight...if you schedule time to rest on advance you know for a fact you are not procrastinating but being disciplined enough to rest periodically and systematically."},{"role":"user","content":"Reply by Harrison Todd:\n@Scott Northwolf To pick up a draggable item, press the space bar. While dragging, use the arrow keys to move the item. Press space again to drop the item in its new position, or press escape to cancel."},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd how long have you been into self-improvement for? I can feel the vibe from afar, bro..."},{"role":"user","content":"Reply by Harrison Todd:\n@Scott Northwolf About 2 years now."},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd epic! I've been into it for 4 by now... you're using a timetable or habit tracker as well?"},{"role":"user","content":"Reply by Harrison Todd:\n@Scott Northwolf Yeah, extremely powerful tools."},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd core habits?"},{"role":"user","content":"Reply by Harrison Todd:\n@Scott Northwolfdeep work (3+hrs, usually ends up being more like 4-5)cold shower in the morningplan tomorrow todayreading (doing a bit less rn to focus on work, but usually 1.5hrs+ a day)habit + metric trackingwhole food, high protein diet"},{"role":"user","content":"Reply by Harrison Todd:\n@Scott Northwolf what about you?"},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd06:00 Wake up, read self-transcendence document and meditation.07:00 Gratitude journaling.07:10 Reading (right now Principles by Ray Dalio).08:00 Workout09:00 Cold shower09:20 Deep work14:00 Lunch15:00 Deep work18:00 Dinner19:00 Winding down routine21:21 Sleep."},{"role":"user","content":"Reply by Harrison Todd:\n@Scott Northwolf looks really good"},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd core habits are without a shadow of a doubt for me:-Meditation and gratitude journaling (habit stacking with this) for the soul and mental health.-Reading (for the mind).-Workout for the body.-Deep work (there's nothing better than produce value and make money helping people, it's really fun).Deep journaling I don't really count it as one because it's natural to me, like brushing your teeth or taking a shower, it's just a standard."},{"role":"assistant","content":"@Harrison Todd thanks, brother. Likewise for yours..."}]}
